    <p>Twelve reli­gious or­gan­i­sa­tions span­ning mosques, Hindu tem­ples, churches, Bud­dhist tem­ples and gur­d­waras will be al­lowed to hold gath­er­ings of up to 100 peo­ple from Fri­day, as the Gov­ern­ment eased some Covid-19 rules yes­ter­day. This will ap­ply only to con­gre­ga­tional and wor­ship ser­vices.</p>


